ZH: 我不能亲自参加会议，所以请你代替我去。
EN: I can't personally attend the meeting, so please go on my behalf.

ZH: 在我的家人生病期间，我得代替他们照顾家。
EN: During the illness of my family members, I have to take care of the household in their stead.

ZH: 如果你不能出席晚宴，我可以代替你去。
EN: If you're unable to attend the dinner party, I can go in your place.

ZH: 他仍然坚持使用传统的纸质书籍，代替电子阅读方式。
EN: He still insists on using traditional paper books rather than electronic reading.

ZH: 你需要找一个人来代替你在周末工作。
EN: You need to find someone to substitute for you at work on the weekend.

ZH: 胡椒粉可以代替辣椒粉来调味这道菜。
EN: Pepper can be used as a substitute for chili powder to season this dish.

ZH: 这家公司决定要雇佣一个代替他们的首席执行官。
EN: The company has decided to hire a replacement CEO to stand in for them.

ZH: 他紧急有事，无法参加会议，所以另外一位同事代替了他。
EN: He had an emergency and couldn't attend the meeting, so another colleague stood in for him.

ZH: 这个机器人可以代替我们完成重复且繁琐的工作。
EN: This robot can take the place of us to complete repetitive and tedious tasks.

ZH: 出于安全考虑，他们决定将化学品替换成环保的材料。
EN: For safety reasons, they decided to substitute chemicals with environmentally-friendly materials.

ZH: 没有任何东西能代替母爱的温暖和关怀。
EN: Nothing can replace the warmth and care of a mother's love.

ZH: 老师用白板上的彩色标记来代替粉笔。
EN: The teacher used colorful markers on the whiteboard to replace chalk.

ZH: 很多人选择使用天然成分的洗发水代替化学洗发水。
EN: Many people choose to use natural ingredient shampoo instead of chemical-based ones.

ZH: 这种新型电子设备可以代替传统笔记本电脑。
EN: This new electronic device can replace traditional laptops.

ZH: 我们应该用绿色能源来代替化石燃料。
EN: We should use green energy to substitute fossil fuels.

ZH: 在生产过程中，可回收材料被用来代替一次性塑料。
EN: Recyclable materials are used to substitute single-use plastics in the production process.

ZH: 她用坚果和果干代替了零食。
EN: She substituted nuts and dried fruits for snacks.

ZH: 这匹马因伤无法参加比赛，所以需要有人代替。
EN: The horse cannot participate in the race due to injury, so someone needs to substitute.

ZH: 鉴于情况，领导决定代替传统办公室环境，实行远程办公政策。
EN: Given the circumstances, the management decided to substitute the traditional office environment with a remote working policy.

ZH: 接下来的几周内，他将代替老板主持会议。
EN: In the next few weeks, he will stand in for the boss to chair the meetings.
